The Njuri Ncheke council of elders stormed out of a meeting organized by Ameru professionals on Saturday in Chuka University.The elders who marched out of the meeting claimed one of the officials said they should elect new officials in the council.Read: Njuri Ncheke faction heads criticised over pre-poll pactsLed by Chairman Paul M ithinkia and Secretary general Phares Ruteere, the elders accused former PS Francis Muthaura of talking about "secret council issues." "We heard him saying that the supreme council will conduct elections and we are surprised," M ithinkia said on Saturday."The council of elders informed him that his role as patron had been revoked after he politicised the council of elders matters and caused division."M ithinkia said Muthaura should not have talked matters related to the council as the meeting was about Ameru professionals.Read: Wrangles within Njuri Ncheke Council of Elders split MeruM ithinkia said the council ought to be respected and its operations left to them to decide adding "the council has played a big role in the struggle for independence.""We do not have a school where you are taught about how to be a Njuri Ncheke elder it s a big secret and our affairs should be left to us," he said.M ithinkia said the council will not hold elections as Muthaura had earlier said. Professor cannot preside over the supreme council elections he is not the chairman and we stripped him of his role as patron, he said. He said Muthaura should instead concentrate on his role as Lapset boss. Muthaura made the remarks when he was addressing Ameru professionals.Also read: Njuri Ncheke secretary is 'ready to leave'Read: Njuri Ncheke faction heads criticised over pre-poll pacts